OL,3,CWhen will snow hit the UK and how long
OL,4,Cwill it last?
OL,6,FWhy is there a cold snap? Where is it
OL,7,Fcoming from?
OL,9,FCold, Arctic air sunk from the north
OL,10,Fto all areas by the end of last night.
OL,11,FTemperatures are much lower than we've
OL,12,Fbeen used to so far this month - but
OL,13,Fnothing unusual for the time of year.
OL,15,FWe're statistically more likely to see
OL,16,Fsnow in January and February than any
OL,17,Fother months of the year.
